ARTICLE_1_ID=1
ARTICLE_1_TITLE=Java 25 LTS: Virtual Threads hit production at Netflix scale
ARTICLE_1_SOURCE=InfoQ
ARTICLE_1_CATEGORY=JVM
ARTICLE_1_BODY=Netflix migrated 200 services to Virtual Threads and reports 40% more throughput. GC pressure dropped 22% and p99 latency was cut in half. The team highlights that the per-request thread mental model is viable again at scale.

ARTICLE_2_ID=2
ARTICLE_2_TITLE=GitHub Copilot Workspace entra en GA — el dev loop completo se vuelve agéntico
ARTICLE_2_SOURCE=GitHub Blog
ARTICLE_2_CATEGORY=AI Tools
ARTICLE_2_BODY=Copilot now plans, writes code, runs tests, and opens PRs autonomously from a single natural language description. Early adopters report 3x reduction in cycle time for small features.

ARTICLE_3_ID=3
ARTICLE_3_TITLE=Rust supera a Go en benchmarks de APIs backend por 3er año consecutivo
ARTICLE_3_SOURCE=TechEmpower
ARTICLE_3_CATEGORY=Performance
ARTICLE_3_BODY=Actix-web hits 1.2M req/s on commodity hardware. Go Fiber reaches 890k. JVM with Project Loom marks 1.05M req/s on I/O-bound workloads. Spring WebFlux comes in at 760k.

ARTICLE_4_ID=4
ARTICLE_4_TITLE=PostgreSQL 17: replicación lógica amenaza a Kafka para workloads medianos
ARTICLE_4_SOURCE=Postgres Weekly
ARTICLE_4_CATEGORY=Databases
ARTICLE_4_BODY=Sub-10ms latency in CDC makes the message broker optional for teams with less than 50k events/sec. The Outbox Pattern is now first-class in the official pg17 documentation.

ARTICLE_5_ID=5
ARTICLE_5_TITLE=Anthropic publica Claude con tool use paralelo y structured outputs
ARTICLE_5_SOURCE=Anthropic Blog
ARTICLE_5_CATEGORY=AI Models
ARTICLE_5_BODY=Parallel tool invocations and strict JSON mode reduce agentic pipeline latency by 60%. Context window extends for long-running agent loops.
